Capital Markets

Company Overview of Heartland Advisors, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
William John Nasgovitz  Chief Investment Officer, Portfolio Manager, Chairman, and Director, Heartland Advisors, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships73--
Background

		Mr. William John Nasgovitz, also known as Bill, serves as Portfolio Manager of Heartland Group, Inc., Heartland Select Value Fund, Heartland Mid Cap Value Fund & Heartland Value Fund. Mr. Nasgovitz serves as the Chairman, Chief Investment Officer and Portfolio Manager of Heartland Advisors, Inc. Mr. Nasgovitz founded Heartland in 1983 and manages its small-cap value strategy. He was employed at Dain Rauscher Incorporated & Morgan Stanley DW Inc. He served as Chairman, ... Chief Investment Officer and Portfolio Manager of Heartland International Value Fund. He served as Portfolio Manager of Heartland Group, Inc. - Heartland Value Plus Fund. Prior to that, he was employed at Dain Bosworth and The Milwaukee Company from 1978 to 1982. Previously, Mr. Nasgovitz worked at Dean Witter Reynolds from 1968 to 1978. He has extensive industry experience. Mr. Nasgovitz is a Board Member of Milwaukee College Preparatory School and Junior Achievement of Wisconsin. Previously, he was a Director of Capital Investments, Inc. Mr. Nasgovitz is a member of YPO/WPO. He has been recognized by Morningstar as “a veteran micro-cap stock-picker.”. Mr. Nasgovitz served as the Captain of U.S. Air Force from 1968 and 1972. He has earned a B.A. in Business from University of Wisconsin - Madison in 1967.Read Full Background




